title: WHAT'S ON: A taste of weekend events on the Coast
text:
Where: Tour leave from Customs House Interpretive Centre. 
What: Tour through the early days of the HeritageCity 
Cost: $10 Adult, $5 Children 6-17 years 
WHACK FOR WELL-BEING 
When: Friday, from 9am. Where: Hervey Bay Golf Club, Pialba. What: The 2015 Mental Health Week Community Golf Day promoting the benefits of mentally healthy workplaces, individual self-care & the need to address the stigma still apparent when discussing mental health issues within families, relationships, workplaces & the community in general. A shotgun start, 9 Hole- 3 Ball Ambrose. 
SATURDAY 
When: Saturday, 7am-1pm. Where: Pier Park, Urangan. What: Stock up on your fresh fruit and vegetables at the newly opened Urban Farm, which now runs every Saturday. 
BASIC PHOTOGRAPHY WORKSHOP 
When: Saturday, 1pm to 4pm. Where: Hervey Bay Regional Gallery, Pialba. What: Join the fun of learning to control your DSLR. Cost: $15 
When: Saturday, 7.30pm-11.30pm. Where: The Bayswater Bar and Bistro, Urangan. What: Sample over 20 beers, try food matching with craft beer and listen to live mnusic from Mark Deviney. 
RELAY FOR LIFE 
When: Saturday, 3pm-Sunday 9am. Where: Seafront Oval, Pialba. What: Relay For Life is a fun and moving overnight experience that raises vital funds for the Cancer Council's research, prevention, information and support services. 
SUNDAY 
When: Sunday, 6am to noon Where: Kruger Court, Booral Road, Urangan. What: You can find various items at these fantastic markets such as arts and crafts, trash and treasure, cakes, jams, and many other local delights. Cost: Free. 
BAYSIDE TRANSFORMATIONS 5TH BIRTHDAY BARBEQUE 
When: Sunday, 12.30pm. What: Celebrating 5 successful years of operation, and the graduation of a participant. entertainment
